name: Hotel Le Jardin

reviews.review_text: Their food quality, quantity, taste never disappoints. Best place to eat seafood at affordable rates. Staff is quite friendly and service is quick.

The fish is always fresh. The quantity is awesome. The taste of the curries is amazing. This place is a must visit if you want to try Goan food.
It does fair job when it comes to Indian Chinese dishes as well.
You will struggle to park your car, however you can pay park and walk to this place.

Love going here again and again. The ambience reminds of days gone by when restaurants used to be classy and reflected good taste and culture. The wooden floor and decor takes you back to old times. A good Goan setting. The food is good and delicious. Prices are reasonable. Portions are generous. Fish thali is my go to at this place. They have the regular one which comes with Mackerel and special thali comes with Modso/kingfish and a sweet dish. The only issue are the stairs. They are too steep needs great care to go up or climb down. Given the space constraints there could be no option but to have it this way, I think. Car park is a minute away. Two wheelers can park in front of the restaurant. Will visit again
and again.

description:
**A Culinary Escape at Hotel Le Jardin: A Seafood Haven in Goa**

Nestled in the picturesque locale of Assonora, Goa, Hotel Le Jardin boasts an impressive rating of 4.2 from over 1,000 patrons, positioning it as a must-visit destination for food enthusiasts. This charming eatery is particularly celebrated for its **seafood** offerings, with over 30 mentions of fresh catches in customer reviews. Aside from seafood, the restaurant excels in **fish thali**, a local favorite with 14 mentions, and possesses a comfortable ambiance with air conditioning—a relief in Goa’s warm climate.

**Ambiance & Design**

Stepping into Hotel Le Jardin, diners are immediately transported to a world that echoes the elegance of bygone eras. The aesthetic is characterized by warm wooden floors and tasteful décor, creating an inviting atmosphere perfect for cozy meals. Customers have noted the nostalgia-inducing vibes that reflect a refined taste and culture, making each visit feel unique. The restaurant's ambience is enhanced by soft music that further gently envelops guests, allowing them to relax while contemplating the sumptuous menu.

![Wooden Decor](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdnFXKZboJKBlNj1CX2A_0VO9Y-5Rp2Ov2rw8mQ3laXx3iNECdp0Ttqn1POQIOOYXeZXQS71G4Ul_pg5iLGzEjDuXgSMoisfLoXBmArzoX8JS6veOMAqB2JNS6HpyGKaRxy3cLdehA=w375-h563-p)

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The culinary offerings at Hotel Le Jardin showcase a delightful blend of **Goan and Indian cuisine**, with seafood taking center stage. Reviews frequently highlight the restaurant’s **fish thali**, with options including a generous serving of mackerel in the regular version, and a special thali featuring modso/kingfish alongside a delightful sweet dish. Patrons rave about the freshness of the fish and the rich, nuanced flavors of the curries, making it a go-to spot for seafood aficionados. The portions are notably generous and incredibly reasonably priced, ensuring an overall satisfying dining experience.

For those seeking variety, the restaurant also does an admirable job with Indian Chinese dishes, catering to diverse palates. 

![Fish Thali](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdmsuV2FpvludHKJWIxA2MJtm27y71_3DL7tN8CIq2Y6ztj74vVGrjYvqzBJw_G_ITl6pquv6rgHuHufRGhTFcnOu7b_LASMENhDB7koI8gOxBHFDP4fQbCUWo5mDipAjlOMqv4p=w375-h281-p)

**Customer Experience & Service**

The service at Hotel Le Jardin is frequently praised for its efficiency and friendliness. The staff’s attentiveness adds to the overall dining pleasure, ensuring that all needs are promptly met. Although some customers mention challenges with parking—no doubt a minor hurdle given the culinary rewards that await—it appears that this is a small price to pay for the rich flavors inside. Diners are advised that while parking can be tricky, a pay-and-walk option is available, making access easier for those willing to explore the area a bit.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Social media buzz indicates that Hotel Le Jardin has earned its place as a beloved local fixture, as patrons return time and again for the satisfying meals and nostalgic environment. Reviewers often commend the price-to-portion ratio, adding to the positive sentiment surrounding this well-loved eatery. With over 1000 customer reviews reflecting a gracious consensus on quality and service, this culinary gem continues to thrive.

**Visual Content Highlights**

The visually compelling images shared by customers also speak volumes—depicting the warm atmosphere and enticing dishes that await each guest. One can almost smell the sea breeze and taste the freshness reflected in the beautifully plated meals.

![Seafood Delights](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdlVBztq-wwvGhR7g4nLFLzZnkQDX9HecIRJ-1oLtuYKHn86vZ4zi-xO4lS127toHDgBLuxDYiDuilqvg-UDzP4ZP6huXXfbRHhN_Cfggvf4CZA9AAeOECT1R_Vq7bC5x9Xcl-Ws=w375-h281-p)

In conclusion, whether you’re a local or a visiting foodie, Hotel Le Jardin awaits with its delicious seafood, generous portions, and a charming ambience that invites you to linger a little longer. This restaurant is undoubtedly a culinary delight, promising delicious meals and fond memories for those who step through its doors.
